!!!Rule section


!!Consonant rules

!Consonant gradation

* __X:x halflong to short gradation__  mool7â to moolâ



* __x:y gradation __ c to s etc, note that t:đ is in a separate rule



* __t:đ gradation __   for ito : iđo

* __tk:đh gradation__    for atka : ađha


* __xx:x gradation__  tikká:tiká, deleting the first k, etc.




* __xx:y long to something else gradation 1 __   hh:V, kk:h, pp:v, čč:J, deleting first part, k:0 in kk4:h etc


* __xx:y long to something else gradation 2 __  hh:V, kk:h, pp:v, čč:J here we change second part, k4:h in kk4:h etc.



* __yx:zx gradation__  ht:vt, we use h4 





* __xyy:xy gradation A__  Perhaps merge this with next


* __xyy:xy gradation B__  this contains i4 pairs


* __xyy:xy gradation B__  




* __xxy:xy gradation for nnj__  special case



* __xyy:xz gradation for k:h 1__  first k goes to 0

* __xyy:xz gradation for k:h 2 __  second k goes to h

* __xˊy:xy gradation__ , this rule deletes the ˊ mark

* __xˊy:xy gradation for i4__  , this rule deletes the ˊ mark when first consonant is i4




!Other Consonant Rules


* __Consonant shortening (not weak grade)__ pp to p for kappeer ~ kaperist







* __nnj to nj shortening__  special rule, e.g. konnjâl -> konjâlân



* __Lengthen root consonant after vowel shortening__  e.g. tt in hamittist



* __Lengthening of half-long root consonant 1__  for h to vv

* __Lengthening of half-long root consonant 2__   for h to vv


* __Lengthening of short root consonant 1__  for l-dot to ll, changing l7 to first l in ll

* __Lengthening of short root consonant 2__   for l-dot to ll, changing ^RC to second l in ll



* __Lengthening of short root consonant 2__   for l-dot to ll  



* __Assimilation of root consonant and double suffix consonant__  delet t in haamit in front of -ttáá, avoid -tttáá



* __Consonant lengthening after xx:x weak grade__  for locative kassaast, which is lengthened weak grade




* __Consonant lengthening after xx:x weak grade with special consonant on upper side__  as previous rule, but for k4, č4, p4

* __Consonant lengthening after x:y weak grade__  , here we lengthen the lower y consonant, spaha -> spavvaast



* __Consonant lengthening after x:y weak grade with special consonant on upper side__  as previous rule, but for k4, č4, p4












* __Consonant lengthening after h4 initial weak grade__  lengthening weak grade of kk4 gives hh




